form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service, Request That Applicant For Naturalization Appear for interview

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/13/2023 OF U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service Request That Applicant For Naturalization Appear for interview ELIDA BOLANOS Alien Registration no: A90-414-760 9631 FONTAINEBLEAU BLVD. APT. # 201 MIAMI, FL 33172 Date: March 16, 1999 This office has been trying to call you on several occasions and was unable to contact you. Your application for naturalization has been received and arrangements have been made for a follow-up examination on your application. Please come to: IMMIGRATION & INATURALIZATION SERVICE 77 S.E. 5TH STREET 2ND FLOOR MIAMI, FLORIDA 33131 EXAMINER FD MARCH 25,1999 AT: 2:10 pm The proceeding will take about an hour. If for any reasons you cannot keep this appointment, return this letter immediately with your explanation and a request for a new appointment; otherwise, no further action will be take on your application. YOU MUST BRING WITH YOU: * This letter * Alien Registration Receipt Card * A copy of your Alien Registration Receipt Card * Your passports and/or any documents you have which you used in connection with any entries in the United States. * A valid daytime phone number.
